					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2007/07/29/docbyscott.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2007/07/29/doc.jpg&quot; width=&quot;105&quot; height=&quot;138&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; hspace=&quot;15&quot; vspace=&quot;5&quot; alt=&quot;A picture named doc.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot;http://images.del.icio.us/static/js/playtagger.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;I was reading David Weinberger's beautiful &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hyperorg.com/blogger/mtarchive/doc_the_elder.html&quot;&gt;testimonial&lt;/a&gt; to growing older, on the occasion of &lt;a href=&quot;http://doc.weblogs.com/&quot;&gt;Doc's&lt;/a&gt; 60th birthday, which is today!" created="Sun, 29 Jul 2007 16:25:55 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I thought the best birthday present I could give &lt;a href=&quot;http://doc.weblogs.com/2007/07/29#goodPlanetLikeItHereThinkIllStay&quot;&gt;Doc&lt;/a&gt; is the sound of beautiful music on Scripting News. And what song? Dr Dave helped me there. He wrote a gorgeous &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hyperorg.com/blogger/mtarchive/older_than_lennon.html&quot;&gt;piece&lt;/a&gt; about John Lennon, that brought me tears of gratitude for a life that still continues inspire, even though it was cut short by an act of lunacy." created="Sun, 29 Jul 2007 16:33:08 GMT"/>
					<outline text="John Lennon's &lt;a href=&quot;http://mp3.morningcoffeenotes.com/songs/soThisIsChristmas.mp3&quot;&gt;So This is Christmas&lt;/a&gt; isn't strictly a birthday song, but it works anyway. " created="Sun, 29 Jul 2007 16:27:40 GMT"/>
					<outline text="So Doc, you're an old fart for sure, but I love you dearly, and am glad your heart is healthy and you still have your sense of humor! " created="Sun, 29 Jul 2007 16:32:47 GMT"/>
