					<outline text="I got &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.duncanriley.com/2007/07/15/wall-street-journal-tries-to-re-write-blogging-history/#comment-158739&quot;&gt;involved&lt;/a&gt; in the discussion, and along the way dug up an archive.org version of BlogTree.com, specifically the &lt;a href=&quot;http://web.archive.org/web/20041012103912/www.blogtree.com/blogtree.php?blogid=140&quot;&gt;page&lt;/a&gt; for Scripting News." created="Mon, 16 Jul 2007 01:24:54 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wordyard.com/2007/07/15/no-first-blogger/&quot;&gt;Scott Rosenberg&lt;/a&gt;, who started covering blogs in &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.salon.com/tech/col/rose/1999/05/28/weblogs/index.html&quot;&gt;1999&lt;/a&gt; in Salon, responds to the WSJ story." created="Mon, 16 Jul 2007 06:25:19 GMT"/>
