				<outline text="Is Apple breaking my headphones?" created="Mon, 02 Jul 2007 02:59:30 GMT">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.pearlpaint.com/shop~parentID~989~categoryID~988.htm&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2007/07/01/exacto.gif&quot; width=&quot;45&quot; height=&quot;151&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; hspace=&quot;15&quot; vspace=&quot;5&quot; alt=&quot;A picture named exacto.gif&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.kottke.org/07/06/cupertino-we-have-a-problem&quot;&gt;Jason Kottke reports&lt;/a&gt; that you can hack up your &quot;third party&quot; headphones with an Exacto knife to get them to work with the iPhone. " created="Mon, 02 Jul 2007 02:59:38 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Excuse me, but I like my headphones as they are, and the iPhone is a pretty lame iPod, crippled if you ask me, so I'll stick with my 60GB unit and hope that some other manufacturer gets their act together and teaches Apple some manners with their customers' money. " created="Mon, 02 Jul 2007 03:07:20 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Can you imagine the meeting at Apple where they decided that they had the market power to force their customers to get new headphones! Such chutzpah." created="Mon, 02 Jul 2007 03:07:30 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Is Apple breaking the web?" created="Sun, 01 Jul 2007 21:22:03 GMT">
					<outline text="If the iPhone were some little obscure thing then &lt;a href=&quot;http://reader.mac.com/mobile/v1/http%3A%2F%2Fwww.scripting.com%2Frss.xml&quot;&gt;pages like this&lt;/a&gt; wouldn't be such a concern. &lt;a href=&quot;http://flickr.com/photos/scriptingnews/687640692/&quot;&gt;Screen shot&lt;/a&gt;." created="Sun, 01 Jul 2007 21:22:10 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Viewing it by iPhone, it's an RSS reader, viewing this site, that's why it showed up in my referrers. Not clear why it can't be displayed in Firefox on my Mac laptop." created="Sun, 01 Jul 2007 21:22:51 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Attn TwitterGram devs" created="Sun, 01 Jul 2007 21:07:31 GMT">
					<outline text="If you're working on the phone to TG connection, this &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.twittergram.com/#newPhonePost&quot;&gt;new web service&lt;/a&gt;, twitterGram.newPhonePoast, simplifies the problem; makes it easier to implement the connection. " created="Sun, 01 Jul 2007 21:07:38 GMT"/>
